      <h1>State of the Art</h1>
      <h2>Established Concepts and Practices</h2>
      <p>
        The technical evolution has immensely affected how we organise, access, and even conceptualise information (Mutsaers et al., 1998). Various techniques have been created to solve the new challenges. Each takes a different approach, but they all centre on the interconnection of information. This idea is a structural feature as well as a cognitive tool. It allows for networked thinking, in which accessing one piece of knowledge leads to discovering related concepts. This improves comprehension and problem-solving abilities (Alhadad, 2018).
      </p>
      <p>
        Each methodology provides a distinct viewpoint on interconnectedness. They assist users in creating structures that expose the underlying connections between data components. This thesis intends to demonstrate how to use connections for improved knowledge management by examining these.
